.TH OPENME 1 "March 2026" "openme" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
openme \- Single Packet Authentication firewall knocking tool
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B openme
[\fIGLOBAL OPTIONS\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fICOMMAND OPTIONS\fR]
[\fIARGS\fR]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B openme
implements SPA (Single Packet Authentication) using ephemeral
Curve25519 ECDH key exchange, ChaCha20\-Poly1305 AEAD encryption, and
Ed25519 signatures.
.PP
To a port scanner every port is always closed.
Only an authenticated client holding a valid Ed25519 private key can
send a 165\-byte knock packet that temporarily opens a firewall rule on
the server.
The knock packet itself is indistinguishable from random noise;
the server never responds.
After the configurable
.I knock_timeout
(default 30 seconds) the firewall rule is automatically removed.
.PP
The same binary acts as both the server daemon and the client:
.PP
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 4
.B Server commands:
.BR init ", " serve ", " add ", " list ", " revoke
.IP \(bu 4
.B Client commands:
.BR connect ", " status ", " profiles
.RE
.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
These flags must be placed \fIbefore\fR the subcommand name.
.TP
.BI \-\-config " PATH"
Path to the server configuration file.
Default:
.IR /etc/openme/config.yaml .
.TP
.BI \-\-client\-config " PATH"
Path to the client configuration file.
Default:
.IR ~/.openme/config.yaml .
.TP
.BI \-\-log\-level " LEVEL"
Log verbosity.
One of
.IR debug ", " info ", " warn ", " error .
Default:
.IR info .
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print command help and exit.
.
.SH SERVER COMMANDS
.
.SS openme init
.B openme init \-\-server\fR \fIHOSTNAME\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
Initialise a new server configuration.
Generates a fresh Curve25519 keypair and writes a default config file to
.I /etc/openme/config.yaml
(or the path set by
.BR \-\-config ).
.PP
.B Options:
.TP
.BI \-\-server " HOSTNAME"
Public hostname or IP address of this server (required).
Embedded in generated client configs.
.TP
.BI \-\-port " PORT"
UDP (and TCP health\-check) port.
Default:
.IR 54154 .
.TP
.BI \-\-firewall " BACKEND"
Firewall backend.
One of
.IR nft " (default) or " iptables .
.TP
.B \-\-force
Overwrite an existing config without prompting.
.
.SS openme serve
.B openme serve
.PP
Start the SPA server daemon.
Listens on the configured UDP port for knock packets.
Validates each packet (signature, timestamp, replay nonce) and, on
success, opens a temporary firewall rule for the knock source (or target)
IP using the configured backend.
.PP
The daemon blocks until interrupted with
.BR SIGINT " or " SIGTERM ,
at which point all ephemeral firewall rules are closed.
.PP
Intended to be run as a
.BR systemd (1)
service; a unit file is included in the package at
.IR /lib/systemd/system/openme.service .
.
.SS openme add \fINAME\fR
.B openme add
.I NAME
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
Register a new client on the server.
Generates an Ed25519 keypair for the client, appends the public key to
the server config, and prints a ready\-to\-use YAML profile block the
client should copy to
.IR ~/.openme/config.yaml .
.PP
.B Options:
.TP
.B \-\-qr
Display a QR code in the terminal.
Useful for provisioning mobile clients without copy\-paste.
.TP
.BI \-\-qr\-out " FILE"
Write the QR code as a PNG to
.IR FILE .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-privkey
Omit the private key from the QR code.
The mobile app must generate its own keypair and its public key must then
be registered separately with
.BR openme\ add .
.TP
.BI \-\-expires " RFC3339"
Optional key expiry timestamp in RFC\~3339 format (e.g.\&
.IR 2027\-01\-01T00:00:00Z ).
Knocks from this client after the expiry time are rejected.
.TP
.BI \-\-port\-mode " MODE"
Port access mode.
One of
.IR default " (inherit server defaults), " only " (client ports only), or"
.IR default_plus " (defaults plus extra ports)."
Default:
.IR default .
.TP
.BI \-\-port " PORT/PROTO"
Add an extra port rule (e.g.\ \fI2222/tcp\fR).
May be specified multiple times.
Used with
.I default_plus
or
.IR only .
.
.SS openme list
.B openme list
.PP
List all registered clients in the server config.
Output includes the client name, Ed25519 key fingerprint, port mode, and
expiry date.
.
.SS openme revoke \fINAME\fR
.B openme revoke
.I NAME
.PP
Remove a client from the server configuration.
Takes effect immediately for all subsequent knock attempts; no server
restart is required.
.
.SH CLIENT COMMANDS
.
.SS openme connect \fR[\fIPROFILE\fR]
.B openme connect
[\fIPROFILE\fR]
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
Send a single 165\-byte SPA knock packet to the server specified in the
named profile (default:
.IR default ).
On success the server opens a temporary firewall rule.
If
.I post_knock
is set in the profile, the given command is executed immediately after
the knock, making
.B openme connect
a transparent wrapper around
.BR ssh (1)
or any other tool.
.PP
.B Options:
.TP
.BI \-\-ip " ADDRESS"
IP address to open the firewall rule for.
Default:
.I 0.0.0.0
(the source IP of the knock packet as seen by the server).
.
.SS openme status \fR[\fIPROFILE\fR]
.B openme status
[\fIPROFILE\fR]
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
Check whether the server's TCP health port is reachable.
The health port is only open after a successful knock and closes
automatically when the
.I knock_timeout
expires.
.TP
.B \-\-knock
Perform a knock first, then check the health port.
Validates the full SPA authentication round trip end\-to\-end.
.
.SS openme profiles \fR[\fINAME\fR]
.B openme profiles
[\fINAME\fR]
.PP
List all profiles in the client config file.
If
.I NAME
is given, display the full details of that profile.
Sensitive fields (private keys) are always redacted from the output.
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/openme/config.yaml
Server configuration.
Generated by
.BR "openme init" .
Permissions must be
.I 0600
(owner read/write only); the server refuses to start if they are wider.
.TP
.I ~/.openme/config.yaml
Default client profile file.
Contains one or more named profiles.
Each profile holds the server address, UDP port, server public key, and
the client's Ed25519 private key.
Permissions should be
.IR 0600 .
.TP
.I /lib/systemd/system/openme.service
systemd unit file for the server daemon.
Enable with
.BR "systemctl enable \-\-now openme" .
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Server: first-time setup
.nf
# Generate server config and keys
sudo openme init \-\-server myserver.example.com

# Register a client (prints client YAML + optional QR)
sudo openme add alice \-\-qr

# Start the daemon
sudo systemctl enable \-\-now openme
.fi
.SS Client: connect and SSH
.nf
# Store the YAML block printed by 'openme add' in:
#   ~/.openme/config.yaml

# Test reachability (knock first, then check)
openme status \-\-knock

# Knock using the default profile + invoke post_knock automatically
openme connect

# Knock the 'home' profile
openme connect home

# Open a rule for a specific IP address
openme connect \-\-ip 10.0.0.5
.fi
.SS Client: advanced registration
.nf
# Grant alice only ports 22 and 443
sudo openme add alice \-\-port\-mode only \-\-port 22/tcp \-\-port 443/tcp

# Grant bob the defaults plus an extra port; expire the key at end of year
sudo openme add bob \-\-port\-mode default_plus \-\-port 2222/tcp \e
     \-\-expires 2026\-12\-31T23:59:59Z

# Revoke alice's access immediately
sudo openme revoke alice
.fi
.
.SH PROTOCOL
Each knock is a single UDP datagram of exactly
.B 165 bytes:
.PP
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 4
1 byte   \(em protocol version (currently
.BR 0x01 )
.IP \(bu 4
32 bytes \(em client ephemeral Curve25519 public key (per\-knock)
.IP \(bu 4
12 bytes \(em ChaCha20\-Poly1305 AEAD nonce (random, per\-knock)
.IP \(bu 4
56 bytes \(em ciphertext + 16\-byte Poly1305 tag
.IP \(bu 4
64 bytes \(em Ed25519 signature over all preceding fields
.RE
.PP
Key derivation uses HKDF\-SHA\-256 with info string
.IR \(dqopenme\-v1\-chacha20poly1305\(dq .
Full protocol specification:
.I https://openme.merlos.org/docs/protocol/
.
